channel.title: Running a Client! READ!
channel.description:
when trying to open/run a client i get this message: [code]Exception in thread "main" java.lang.NoClassDefFoundError: Jframe Caused by: java.lang.ClassNotFoundException: Jframe at java.net.URLClassLoader$1.run(Unknown Source) at java.security.AccessController.doPrivileged(Native Method) at java.net.URLClassLoader.findClass(Unknown Source) at java.lang.ClassLoader.loadClass(Unknown Source) at sun.misc.Launcher$AppClassLoader.loadClass(Unknown Source) at java.lang.ClassLoader.loadClass(Unknown Source) Could not find the main class: Jframe. Program will exit. Press any key to continue . . .[/code]
how do i fix this??

item.title: Running a Client! READ!
item.dc:creator: @WaleedScape WaleedScape
item.description:
@WaleedScape wrote:

It cant find the Jframe class. make sure you didnt delete it

item.dc:creator: @Nameme123 Nameme123
item.description:
@Nameme123 wrote:

All you need to do is make sure you have a JFrame.class and if you don’t then edit the run.bat and change the Jframe to Gui or EGUI
